data.text:
Opposition lawmaker and leader of Hong Kong's pro-democracy Frontier political group, Emily Lau, holds up an election campaign leaflet as she addresses a pre-elections political forum held at the Hong Kong Foreign Correspondents Club Tuesday, Aug. 17, 2004. Lau criticized Hong Kong's Liberal Party and it's leader James Tien, who will run against her in the same constituency in the upcoming legislative elections, for changing its stance to withdraw support for full democracy in the near term. (AP Photo/Anat Givon)
